  "texts": [
    "First, it normalises the score for the increase in central bank communication over time.",
    "Second, it normalises the score taking into account the strong heterogeneity between central banks in their frequencies of communication.",
    "Third, it creates a relative measures of policy linkages, disregarding non-relevant communication.",
    "Different kind of policy linkages -dominance and coordination -are to be interpreted as a trade-off, namely more monetary dominance implies less fiscal and financial dominance and coordination.",
    "A relative index is thus an intuitive way to describe the linkage of monetary and other policies."
